{"word":"H157 - אָהַב - ʼâhab - aw-hab' - Love - அன்பு","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong>אָהַב"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>ʼâhab"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>aw-hab'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Love / அன்பு"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"வினைச் சொல்."},{"paragraph":"- நேசமாயிரு. பிரியமாயிரு. அன்பாயிரு, சிநேகமாயிரு. விருப்பமாயிரு. பட்சமாயிரு. அன்புகூர், அன்புவை, சிநேகி, வாஞ்சி,ஆசை வை, மோகங்கொள்."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"(1) to love"},{"paragraph":"(a) (in the Qal)"},{"paragraph":"(1) human love for another, includes love for family and sexual love"},{"paragraph":"(2) human appetite for objects such as food, drink, sleep, wisdom"},{"paragraph":"(3) human love for God or toward God"},{"paragraph":"(4) the act of being a friend"},{"paragraph":"(a) lover (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(b) friend (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(5) God's love toward mankind"},{"paragraph":"(a) towardindividual men"},{"paragraph":"(b) toward people Israel"},{"paragraph":"(c) to righteousness"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"(b) (in the Niphal)"},{"paragraph":"(1) lovely (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(2) lovable (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(c) (in the Piel)"},{"paragraph":"(1) friends"},{"paragraph":"(2) lovers (figuratively used of adulterers)"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"(2) to like"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> A primitive root; to <i>have affection</i> for (sexually or otherwise): - (be-) love (-d, -ly, -r), like, friend."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/